'''Greenford''' is a suburb in the [[London Borough of Ealing]] in [[West London]], England. It was historically an ancient parish in the county of [[Middlesex]]. The most prominent landmarks in the suburb are the [[A40 road|A40]], a large road that connects [[Central London]] with the [[M40 motorway]], [[Horsenden Hill]] {{convert|85|m|ft}} above sea level, the small [[Parish Church]] of Holy Cross (14th century) and Betham House, built by Edward Betham (c. 1780).

