==Political representation==
Greenford is part of the [[Ealing North (UK Parliament constituency)|Ealing North]] UK [[parliament]]ary [[constituency]], represented since 1997 by [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] [[Stephen Pound]].

Greenford is made up of three and a half [[electoral ward]]s for [[local council]] [[election]]s: Greenford Broadway, Greenford Green, North Greenford and half of the Lady Margaret Ward. This is situated on the south side of Greenford Broadway. These wards all elect councillors to [[London Borough of Ealing|Ealing Council]]. Ealing Council is currently run by a Conservative administration.

Political status of Ealing Council:
* [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]]: 43 seats
* [[British Labour Party|Labour]]: 23 seats
* [[Liberal Democrats]]: 3 seats

Greenford is in the [[London Assembly]] [[constituency]] of [[Ealing and Hillingdon]] which has one assembly member: [[Richard Barnes (British politician)|Richard Barnes]] (Conservative), who was re-elected in May 2008.

